[[File:Lyngsjo church Sweden 6.jpg|thumb|The baptismal font in Lyngsjö Church, a work by Tove]] '''Tove''' was a sculptor and [[stonemasonry|stonemason]] active in [[Scania]] during the [[Middle Ages]]. The artist made and signed the [[baptismal font]] of [[Gumlösa Church]] with the words ''Tove gierhi'' ("Tove made me"). Gumlösa Church was inaugurated in 1191. Tove also made the baptismal font in [[Lyngsjö Church]] and perhaps [[Bjäresjö Church]], both also in Scania.<ref name=historiska>{{cite web |url= http://medeltidbild.historiska.se/medeltidbild/typforemal/dopfuntar/stenmastarna.asp|title= Vilka var stenmästarna?|language=Swedish|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date= |website= |publisher= [[Swedish History Museum]]|access-date=4 May 2015}}</ref><ref name=svuppslagsbok>{{cite web |url= http://svenskuppslagsbok.se/80531/tove-medeltida-stenmastare/|title= Tove, medeltida stenmästare|language=Swedish|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date= |website= Svenskuppslagsbok|publisher= |access-date=4 May 2015}}</ref>
